<br>
I personally think that Everquest is not a game for the &quot;PvPer.&quot;  It is more of a game for the &quot;Achiever.&quot;<br>
<br>
To much bias goes on with GM's in combination with restrictions to what you can and can't do.  <br>
<br>
So I don't think there is really a big difference in &quot;red&quot; and &quot;blue&quot; servers?<br>
<br>
Comments? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tyvenn>Tyvenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Baby Seal</span><br>  Posts: 594<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 6:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.broadpark.no/~bsvenhe/tyvimg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: opinion</span><hr size=1> There is definatly a difference.<br>
<br>
Playing on blue servers is very frustrating, atleast when you come from a red. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=synnge>Synnge </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 1:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: opinion</span><hr size=1> the idea of red servers was to have player governed environment. When there are disputes on a blue server, they typically need a gm to get involved. While on a red server a war typically takes place or a meeting of guild minds ensues.<br>
<br>
To bad GM's get involved, and with them not having a standard viewpoint it tends to be the luck of the draw as to what the end result will be.<br>
<br>
Grief players was not the goal, just a byproduct of a bad pvp system, along with immaturity of the player base. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 3:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: opinion</span><hr size=1> Yeah Synnge, I can see it from your point.  And I'm not taking a side here but when a guild and AD had a problem the GM's favored them.  Or at least thats what it seemed to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pyrosprial007>Pyrosprial007</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kick Me</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 3:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: opinion</span><hr size=1> you're a bitchface too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 3:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: opinion</span><hr size=1> heh, me?  ...  quality <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khardrosie>KhardrosIE</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.freebsd.org/gifs/dae_up3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 5:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> so by &quot;a guild&quot; you mean a member of the Rebirth group?  I can honestly say that i don't think AD has been unfair in any of dealings I've ever had.  I think on rallos generally if you're an asshole you get what you deserve.  it's honestly probably the best high end server, unless you're an asshole. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 7:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> No, I'm not saying it's AD.  I am saying when they have a problem usually the GM's favor them.  And if AD does something wrong it may very well be over-looked.  This is due to the fact that the GM's are regular people with regular opinions.  <br>
<br>
They should re-structure the GM and Guide system to somehow be an un-bias position.  I mean it's hard because they are people.  But I think it could be done.<br>
<br>
All of the GM's don't seem to favor the &quot;dark&quot; side of the game.  I think it would be cool to see like a &quot;star war&quot; type GM system.  Where there are evil GM's and there are your good GM's. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A> at: 11/2/02 7:57:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dracaenarallos>DracaenaRallos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 9:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rebirth</span><hr size=1> Although I am not well known, nor highly vocal I fought many long battles both with PB and with Rebirth. I would honestly say that although I have seen people pull trains on us, and AE rain us during ToV raids *cough* Luadian *cough*, I think that people like Steve and Zach pulling some of the biggest trains you can imagine to AD and/or Synergy raids justifies at least some of the retalliation, although the damage shield/faction usage in Rivervale was very gay, *cough* Adell, I figured with PB flying high over my head, I, in their minds had it coming. This kind of thing is what make RZ great, sure GM's and Guides may have believed AD more then Rebirth, but I would have too, the reputation preceding some of the people in Rebirth was huge, even to me when I knew nothing of the old-school RZ end-game. Anyway, blue servers are for the people who like it, and even with a beyond broken PvP system, I wouldn't play on one if you paid me.<br>
<br>
Drac. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(11/2/02 10:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rebirth</span><hr size=1> I'm just saying to limit bias they should make a clan composed of an evil GM and Guides.  Like Greek mythology with the evil immortals and the good immortals.<br>
<br>
IMO that would make the game twice as fun.  You would have someone of a high status backing what you deemed fair.  I don't think it will ever happen.  Hopefully they implemented good things into EQ2...  If anyone will even play it.<br>
<br>
BTW, who is planning on playing it?  I know if I logged 100+, 200+, days on EQ, that I would have to do some thinking.  I don't think Verant should have made a sequal to a MMORPG.  I don't know how you can.  Like they said:  Your in our world now:  A world that is coming to an end. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avaze>Avaze</A> at: 11/2/02 10:35:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vorgevilescale>Vorge Vilescale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vorge Van Gogh</span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 7:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1533.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/bigsuperpaco/girdancing.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rebirth</span><hr size=1> Some people just arent into pvp.  Plain and simple, I know if my RL friends didnt make me start on Rallos I sure as fuck wouldnt be playing on PvP.  But thats me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Adios.<br>
